ABOUT WESTWOOD
Westwood
2014-03-26T16:58:35+00:00

Welcome to Westwood
At Westwood, our investment management teams follow time-tested investment disciplines and put our clients first. This is how we’ve weathered some of the most challenging markets in history.
Susan M. Byrne founded Westwood in 1983 out of a fierce personal commitment to give investors a trustworthy investment solution. To this day, every one of us carries on her commitment to protect our clients’ capital. This singular approach has earned the trust of institutional, private wealth, and mutual fund investors.

Pure focus. Our investment teams are focused on the conservative, investment management philosophies that have helped our clients succeed over multiple market cycles.
Solid foundation. We are a public company with a strong balance sheet, ample cash on hand, and employee shareholders who enjoy coming to work every day.
Powerful performance. We generate competitive results for our clients and have done so for over 30 years.

Whether you manage personal investments or are responsible for a pension, trust, or other pool of assets, you will discover that Westwood is a truly different kind of investment company: one that puts you first.
Come and see for yourself
A visit to one of the Westwood offices is perhaps the best way to see how deeply we value talent, commitment and heart. You’ll see corridors lined with photos of our employees’ world travels, pictures of family and friends in the lounge, and tributes to service and commitment that honor the long tenures of our team members and the many ways they serve the community. We welcome you as a guest, so please contact us for a visit today.



































	Institutional Investing, Wealth Management, Mutual Funds, | Westwood Holdings Group	


























































 




 


















Welcome to Westwood
Westwood
2014-03-10T21:40:36+00:00

Welcome to Westwood
Westwood is a global asset management firm serving institutional investors, private wealth clients and financial intermediaries. Westwood investment management teams in Dallas, Texas, Toronto, Canada, and Boston, MA manage investment strategies across the following areas - U.S. Value equity, Master Limited Partnerships (MLPs), Multi-Asset, Global and Emerging Markets equities and Global Convertibles.
At Westwood, our investment teams follow time-tested disciplines and we put our clients first. This is how we’ve weathered some of the most challenging markets in history and why we continue to provide competitive investment returns, excellent client service and value to our shareholders.


U.S. Institutional Investors

			Westwood helps institutional investors including corporate and public pension plans, endowments, foundations and other institutional clients achieve their goals by offering differentiated investment strategies with comprehensive risk management.




Private Wealth Investors
Westwood Trust provides customized wealth management services to high net worth investors and families as well as select foundations, endowments and corporations. We help our clients grow and protect their capital through innovative wealth management solutions incorporated within our proven multi-asset Enhanced Balanced™ portfolio.




Mutual Funds Investors
Westwood Funds provides individual investors with access to the same portfolio management teams and investment process that leading institutions, endowments and private wealth clients have relied upon for over 30 years.




Non-U.S. Investors
Westwood helps Non-U.S. Investors including corporate and public pension plans, sovereign wealth funds, and other institutional clients achieve their goals by offering differentiated investment strategies with comprehensive risk management. 




Investor Relations
Westwood became a public company in 2002 and has been adding significant shareholder value since that time. We manage our business with a similar approach to the companies we invest in. Westwood maintains a liquid balance sheet with no debt and we do not employ leverage. 


Contact UsClient AccessAbout WestwoodWestwood wins 2016 Best Places to Work in Money Management by Pensions & Investments for the third year in a row.
 
 




































